div class = \"text-block\">The day before the experiment, inoculate 3 mL YPD or SC medium with a single colony. Grow overnight at 30\u00b0C.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948495,"guid":"2A2756509E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948493,"previous_guid":"102578409E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F792A0CE113549F0979BBDD508E6CB73","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Yeast culture and harvest"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B76F3F17509E423493CB7A121613A39F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Harvest cells in a 50 mL conical tube at 1,500 x g for 1 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948496,"guid":"2BB7BA509E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948495,"previous_guid":"2A2756509E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B53917746E924D40A22C1DD0B498C3C0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Yeast culture and harvest"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"85F52566DE584024A204C35CED44FA30","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wash cells 3 x 1 mL Buffer A. Transfer cells to a 1.5 mL tube with the first wash and spin as above between washes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948498,"guid":"3931E4809E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948496,"previous_guid":"2BB7BA509E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2574DFD46E004E99B65A057568312738","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"ChEC"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0EA2B05684964FE98EA0519AC32653CF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Permeabilize cells. Resuspend pellet in 600 \u00b5L Buffer A + 0.1% digitonin (add 30 \u00b5L 2% digitonin in DMSO to 570 \u00b5L Buffer A) and incubate at 30\u00b0C for 5 min. Remove 100 \u00b5L as zero timepoint prior to step 6.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948500,"guid":"5F533EC09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948501,"previous_guid":"6A8D15E09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"22C4896AEBE541369E6101810CF2C25E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BEFAC4D6551B44449B4C7673C5B24C83","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Extract nucleic acids. Add 200 \u00b5L phenol\/chloroform\/isoamyl alcohol, mix well, and spin at max. speed for 5 min in a microfuge. Transfer aqueous phases to new tubes, add 2 \u00b5L (10 \u00b5g) linear acrylamide and 500 \u00b5L 100% ethanol, mix, and precipitate at -80\u00b0C for \u226530 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948501,"guid":"6A8D15E09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948516,"previous_guid":"1A9E2CD09E1F11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"87972D95EA9B471AAEBAE0F696C454AC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4FA2026713FC411E811CB47BAA311427","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 2 \u00b5L 20 mg\/mL proteinase K. Digest protein at 55\u00b0C for 20 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948502,"guid":"7B9066D09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948500,"previous_guid":"5F533EC09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0A8101F4EB344DFEB48FBEB1891EC233","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A4117C0142484C36A54A4BB20CB91469","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Spin at max speed and 4\u00b0C for 10 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948503,"guid":"80344C609E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948502,"previous_guid":"7B9066D09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4B30D0BB3D34490882EF88A165FA1D23","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"96BD6E66971142F58DEB27EA74681C6A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wash pellet with 1 mL 75% ethanol and aspirate ethanol.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948504,"guid":"88D63A909E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948503,"previous_guid":"80344C609E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0B90A470323B4602BB4124085F149DD2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C1058A81DE824380BB39CC45BC53E0CE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Briefly air-dry pellets and resuspend in 29 \u00b5L Qiagen EB or comparable buffer + 1 \u00b5L 10 mg\/mL RNase A and incubate at 37\u00b0C for 10 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948505,"guid":"8FB877609E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948504,"previous_guid":"88D63A909E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0C9B4D2A20B24325B9802F17CED16F9B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AB130BE9366E4149BF86EF66EBEC428A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Run 5 \u00b5L RNase-treated DNA on a 1.5% agarose gel to check DNA fragmentation if desired.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948506,"guid":"95828D709E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948505,"previous_guid":"8FB877609E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"357EEB0AE0AF4D2AA58253DF3F5BFF80","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"76B02CE8CD8340C282B266D2B7296857","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dilute RNase-treated DNA to 200 \u00b5L with Qiagen EB or comparable buffer.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948507,"guid":"9C62A7609E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948506,"previous_guid":"95828D709E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1C3BEC41EC5C4ECBBB223E53ACD6363B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A31F57BDDCCE4C4FAB20353A2E24E180","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 160 \u00b5L Ampure beads (0.8:1 beads:sample ratio) and pipet up and down 10X to mix. Incubate at room temperature for 5 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948508,"guid":"A2111F209E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948507,"previous_guid":"9C62A7609E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AABEE3392A41412A9F36BDBD836DABFC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FCFF207AB317401B8716F6D309D9FB6A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Collect beads on magnetic rack for 2 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948509,"guid":"A6C901E09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948508,"previous_guid":"A2111F209E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"253B8CDA59BE4E40BDEABC4B4222A8DD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9F9425C2D49548E69F38D1FD77E30BE7","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove the supernantant (~400 \u00b5L) to a new tube containing 16 \u00b5L 5 M NaCl (~200 mM final).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948510,"guid":"AE7B87009E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948509,"previous_guid":"A6C901E09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EE9E39F713EB403982BAD0231BA653AB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FC269D27B0034B28B4BFA84C1FB4E8E2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Extract DNA from the unbound fraction. Add 400 \u00b5L phenol\/chloroform\/isoamyl alcohol, mix well, and spin at max. speed for 5 min in a microfuge. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948511,"guid":"B584D3D09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948510,"previous_guid":"AE7B87009E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3A234EBF947C4431825457C9429D0F7D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1B7EF589607B4EE2B46E08EEDAEA8F3D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer aqueous phases to new tubes, add 2 \u00b5L (10 \u00b5g) linear acrylamide and 1 mL 100% ethanol, mix, and precipitate at -80C for \u226530 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948512,"guid":"BDEEC2109E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948511,"previous_guid":"B584D3D09E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5259627A18C34335B25BAB174653B71A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7D6574CED4B94CEFB5D1B897A62E97A6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Spin at max speed and 4\u00b0C for 10 min.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948513,"guid":"C1EBB9409E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948512,"previous_guid":"BDEEC2109E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E2CDE70CEA724D74A570626D80137CAC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AA31E178E4C243D0A565B1182FD212C4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wash pellets with 1 mL 75% ethanol and remove ethanol with vacuum.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948514,"guid":"C76A47609E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948513,"previous_guid":"C1EBB9409E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"062558A17D254B36B584C0716B5DB0F9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Size selection"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7864F0DC7E5549A990C9B506AFD43B7B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Briefly air-dry pellets and resuspend in 25 \u00b5L Qiagen EB or comparable buffer. Recovered DNA can be quantified by Qubit and the size distribution analyzed via TapeStation using a high-sensitivity tape. Sequencing libraries can be prepared using any standard ChIP-seq-style method.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948515,"guid":"15E427309E1F11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948498,"previous_guid":"3931E4809E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A6A35E7AE9A64DFD8427C655AB100530","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"ChEC"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BCDDE65CEF7048AC8B59FAE39DA6CE2C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Add 1.1 \u00b5L 1 M CaCl<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> (~2 mM final), mix, and incubate at 30\u00b0C.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"DB7C1A6E82754DCCBB0A74EB36B2527B","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">A recent study mapping the genome-wide distribution of components of the SAGA and TFIID coactivator complexes (PMID 31913117) with ChEC used a 10-fold lower calcium concentration with a 5 min digestion time in order to minimize background genomic digestion and overdigestion of target sites.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948516,"guid":"1A9E2CD09E1F11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948515,"previous_guid":"15E427309E1F11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"90AB18619581462C897E2D2BEDD84965","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"ChEC"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B949CD323B6546D5B25299A3A2E4C91A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">At each desired time point, remove a 100 \u00b5L aliquot of the digest to a tube containing 90 \u00b5L stop solution and 10 \u00b5L 10% SDS and vortex to mix.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"FC349736AD4C494DBE5D2206B777D72F","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">We have performed multiple time course ChEC experiments for both MNase-tagged factors and free MNase in distinct genetic backgrounds. For free MNase, we have observed that relatively long digestion times (\u2265 2.5 min) yield cleavage of promoter nucleosome-depleted regions and nucleosome linkers due to their accessibility. It is therefore difficult to determine if enrichment of a particular factor is specific at these later time points. However, free MNase signal is quite low at short time points, allowing clear distinction between MNase-tagged factor and free MNase signal. We therefore recommend that, once an initial time course to determine the digestion kinetics of the factor under study and its corresponding free MNase control is performed, short time points be used for further experiments. We have found that a \u2264 1 min digestion is sufficient for all tested factors using the digestion conditions provided here.<\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/cb317a98d402754525430290b8dd5d487aad3e1053c47e1c1bec4db354dfddaf\/b9uqbxd6.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":[{"id":12,"title":"Critical step","icon":"CriticalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":948517,"guid":"AF19FF009E2011EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","previous_id":948514,"previous_guid":"C76A47609E1E11EA81D2BB2CAA5B8DB3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"742181BBA9F64E5DBD084B3BC01E7239","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Data processing and analysis"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B91BCEFE856F4FE39B14D5DD7DB20E9A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>We align paired-end Illumina fastq files to the sacCer3 genome assembly with Bowtie 2 using additional parameters (-I 10 -X 700 --no-unal --no-mixed --no-discordant --dovetail). We then convert alignment SAM files to BAM format with SAMtools and use deepTools <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">bamCoverage<\/span><span> to generate bigWig coverage tracks with single-base resolution (-bs 1), counts per million normalization (--normalizeUsing CPM), and extension of reads to their paired-end fragment length (-e). Further analysis can be done as for ChIP-seq (e.g. peak calling using MACS2 and motif discovery with MEME or HOMER).<\/span><\/div><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/cb317a98d402754525430290b8dd5d487aad3e1053c47e1c1bec4db354dfddaf\/b9usbxd6.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"8BFF5031085A450181CC8850FC8CB2F9","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"de